'''Brunoise''' is a [[French]] term for a very fine dice, usually performed on vegetables. It is used to describe a method of cutting vegetables, usually to the dimensions of 2 mm by 2 mm by 2 mm or less, and is produced by [[julienning]] a vegetable first, and then cutting it many times at a 90 degree [[angle]] to the julienne. This produces the exact dice needed, and the result is often used as a [[garnish]]. The term can also refer to a mixture of [[Leek (vegetable)|leek]]s, [[celery]], and [[carrot]]s chopped in the way described.

